tvm_instructions.name: RUNVMX
tvm_instructions.short: Runs child VM with `code` and stack `x_1...x_n`. Returns the resulting stack `x'_1...x'_m` and exitcode. Other arguments and return values are enabled by flags taken from the stack.

tvm_instructions.name: IFRET
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is non-zero, ends the current continuation and returns to `c0`.

tvm_instructions.name: IFNOTRET
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is zero, ends the current continuation and returns to `c0`.

tvm_instructions.name: IF
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is non-zero, executes `body`, otherwise does nothing.

tvm_instructions.name: IFNOT
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is zero, executes `body`, otherwise does nothing.

tvm_instructions.name: IFJMP
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is non-zero, jumps to `body`, otherwise does nothing.

tvm_instructions.name: IFNOTJMP
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is zero, jumps to `body`, otherwise does nothing.

tvm_instructions.name: IFELSE
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is non-zero, executes `body`, otherwise executes `else`.

tvm_instructions.name: CONDSEL
tvm_instructions.short: If integer `f` is non-zero, returns `x`, otherwise returns `y`.

tvm_instructions.name: CONDSELCHK
tvm_instructions.short: If integer `f` is non-zero, returns `x`, otherwise returns `y`. Throws if `x` and `y` have different types.

tvm_instructions.name: IFRETALT
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is non-zero, ends the current continuation and returns to `c1`.

tvm_instructions.name: IFNOTRETALT
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is zero, ends the current continuation and returns to `c1`.

tvm_instructions.name: REPEAT
tvm_instructions.short: Executes continuation `body` `n`-times, if integer `n` is non-negative.

tvm_instructions.name: REPEATEND
tvm_instructions.short: Takes a remainder of the current continuation and executes it `n`-times, if integer `n` is non-negative.

tvm_instructions.name: UNTIL
tvm_instructions.short: Executes continuation `body`, then pops an integer `cond` from the resulting stack. If `cond` is **zero**, performs another iteration of this loop, otherwise ends the loop.

tvm_instructions.name: UNTILEND
tvm_instructions.short: Takes a remainder of the current continuation, executes it, then pops an integer `cond` from the resulting stack. If `cond` is **zero**, performs another iteration of this loop, otherwise ends the loop.

tvm_instructions.name: WHILE
tvm_instructions.short: Executes continuation `cond`, then pops an integer `cond` from the resulting stack. If `cond` is **non-zero**, executes `body`, and then begins a new iteration, otherwise ends the loop.

tvm_instructions.name: WHILEEND
tvm_instructions.short: Executes continuation `cond`, then pops an integer `cond` from the resulting stack. If `cond` is **non-zero**, takes a remainder of the current continuation and executes it as the loop body, then begins a new iteration, otherwise ends the loop.

tvm_instructions.name: AGAIN
tvm_instructions.short: Executes continuation `body` infinitely many times.

tvm_instructions.name: AGAINEND
tvm_instructions.short: Takes a remainder of the current continuation and executes it infinitely many times.

tvm_instructions.name: REPEATBRK
tvm_instructions.short: Stores current continuation in `c1` of `body` and executes continuation `body` `n`-times, if integer `n` is non-negative.

tvm_instructions.name: REPEATENDBRK
tvm_instructions.short: Stores current continuation in `c1` and takes a remainder of the current continuation and executes it `n`-times, if integer `n` is non-negative.

tvm_instructions.name: UNTILBRK
tvm_instructions.short: Stores current continuation in `c1` of `body` and executes continuation `body`, then pops an integer `cond` from the resulting stack. If `cond` is **zero**, performs another iteration of this loop, otherwise ends the loop.

tvm_instructions.name: UNTILENDBRK
tvm_instructions.short: Stores current continuation in `c1` and takes a remainder of the current continuation, executes it, then pops an integer `cond` from the resulting stack. If `cond` is **zero**, performs another iteration of this loop, otherwise ends the loop.

tvm_instructions.name: WHILEBRK
tvm_instructions.short: Stores current continuation in `c1` of `body` and executes continuation `cond`, then pops an integer `cond` from the resulting stack. If `cond` is **non-zero**, executes `body`, and then begins a new iteration, otherwise ends the loop.

tvm_instructions.name: WHILEENDBRK
tvm_instructions.short: Stores current continuation in `c1` and executes continuation `cond`, then pops an integer `cond` from the resulting stack. If `cond` is **non-zero**, takes a remainder of the current continuation and executes it as the loop body, then begins a new iteration, otherwise ends the loop.

tvm_instructions.name: AGAINBRK
tvm_instructions.short: Store current continuation in `c1` of `body` and executes continuation `body` infinitely many times.

tvm_instructions.name: AGAINENDBRK
tvm_instructions.short: Stores current continuation in `c1` and takes a remainder of the current continuation and executes it infinitely many times.

tvm_instructions.name: SETCONTCTRMANYX
tvm_instructions.short: Sets multiple control registers in a continuation by a `mask`.

tvm_instructions.name: TRY
tvm_instructions.short: Executes `body` and if it throws an exception, transfers control to `handler`.

tvm_instructions.name: THROWANY
tvm_instructions.short: Throws an exception with error code `num` and parameter set to zero. Parameter represents the additional information passed to the exception handler.

tvm_instructions.name: THROWARGANY
tvm_instructions.short: Throws an exception with error code `num` and parameter set to `x`. Parameter represents the additional information passed to the exception handler.

tvm_instructions.name: THROWANYIFNOT
tvm_instructions.short: Throws an exception with error code `num` and parameter set to zero only if `cond` is EQUAL to 0. Parameter represents the additional information passed to the exception handler.

tvm_instructions.name: THROWARGANYIFNOT
tvm_instructions.short: Throws an exception with error code `num` and parameter set to `x` taken from the stack only if `cond` is EQUAL to 0. Parameter represents the additional information passed to the exception handler.

tvm_instructions.name: EQINT
tvm_instructions.short: Compares `x` from stack and `y` from arguments for equality and returns `-1` if equal and `0` otherwise.

tvm_instructions.name: LESSINT
tvm_instructions.short: Compares `x` from stack and `y` from arguments for less than and returns `-1` if true and `0` otherwise.

tvm_instructions.name: GTINT
tvm_instructions.short: Compares `x` from stack and `y` from arguments for greater than and returns `-1` if true and `0` otherwise.

tvm_instructions.name: NEQINT
tvm_instructions.short: Compares `x` from stack and `y` from arguments for inequality and returns `-1` if true and `0` otherwise.

tvm_instructions.name: QEQINT
tvm_instructions.short: Compares `x` from stack and `y` from arguments for equality and returns `-1` if equal and `0` otherwise. Returns `NaN` if operand is `NaN`.

tvm_instructions.name: QLESSINT
tvm_instructions.short: Compares `x` from stack and `y` from arguments for less than and returns `-1` if true and `0` otherwise. Returns `NaN` if operand is `NaN`.

tvm_instructions.name: QGTINT
tvm_instructions.short: Compares `x` from stack and `y` from arguments for greater than and returns `-1` if true and `0` otherwise. Returns `NaN` if operand is `NaN`.

tvm_instructions.name: QNEQINT
tvm_instructions.short: Compares `x` from stack and `y` from arguments for inequality and returns `-1` if true and `0` otherwise. Returns `NaN` if operand is `NaN`.

tvm_instructions.name: SETCONTCTRMANY
tvm_instructions.short: Sets multiple control registers in a continuation by a `mask`.

tvm_instructions.name: TRYARGS
tvm_instructions.short: Executes `body` with `p` top elements from the stack and if it throws an exception, transfers control to `handler`, otherwise copies the top `r` stack elements of the resulting stack of `body` as return values.

tvm_instructions.name: PREPAREDICT
tvm_instructions.short: Prepares the continuation in `c3` for execution along with the integer `num` as an argument. Essentially it's a preparation for method call with `num` ID in the dictionary.

tvm_instructions.name: THROWARG
tvm_instructions.short: Throws an exception with exit code `x` taken from the stack.

tvm_instructions.name: THROWARGIF
tvm_instructions.short: Conditionally throws an exception with error code `x` taken from stack if `cond` is NOT EQUAL to 0.

tvm_instructions.name: THROWARGIFNOT
tvm_instructions.short: Conditionally throws an exception with error code `x` taken from stack if `cond` is EQUAL to 0.

tvm_instructions.name: SETINDEXQ
tvm_instructions.short: Sets the `i`-th component of _Tuple_ `t` to `x`. If `i` is bigger than tuple length, extends the tuple with Nulls first.

tvm_instructions.name: BLESSARGS
tvm_instructions.short: Transforms a _Slice_ into a simple ordinary continuation and sets `r` arguments and `n` missing arguments.

tvm_instructions.name: STIR
tvm_instructions.short: Stores a signed `width`-bit integer `x` into _Builder_ `b` and returns the resulting _Builder_ `b'`.

tvm_instructions.name: STUR
tvm_instructions.short: Stores an unsigned `width`-bit integer `x` into _Builder_ `b` and returns the resulting _Builder_ `b'`.

tvm_instructions.name: IFBITJMP
tvm_instructions.short: If `i`-th bit is set in integer `x`, jumps to `body`, otherwise does nothing.

tvm_instructions.name: IFNBITJMP
tvm_instructions.short: If `i`-th bit is NOT set in integer `x`, jumps to `body`, otherwise does nothing.

tvm_instructions.name: PUSHPOW2
tvm_instructions.short: Quietly pushes `2 ^ x`.

tvm_instructions.name: IFREF
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is non-zero, executes `body` stored in code cell reference, otherwise does nothing.

tvm_instructions.name: IFNOTREF
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is zero, executes `body` stored in code cell reference, otherwise does nothing.

tvm_instructions.name: IFJMPREF
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is non-zero, jumps to `body` stored in code cell reference, otherwise does nothing.

tvm_instructions.name: IFNOTJMPREF
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is zero, jumps to `body` stored in code cell reference, otherwise does nothing.

tvm_instructions.name: IFREFELSE
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is non-zero, executes the continuation stored in cell reference `body`, otherwise executes `else` continuation from the stack.

tvm_instructions.name: IFELSEREF
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is non-zero, executes `body` from the stack, otherwise executes the continuation stored in cell reference `else`.

tvm_instructions.name: IFREFELSEREF
tvm_instructions.short: If `cond` is non-zero, executes the continuation stored in cell reference `body`, otherwise executes the continuation stored in cell reference `else`.

tvm_instructions.name: IFBITJMPREF
tvm_instructions.short: If `i`-th bit is set in integer `x`, jumps to `body` stored in code cell reference, otherwise does nothing.

tvm_instructions.name: IFNBITJMPREF
tvm_instructions.short: If `i`-th bit is NOT set in integer `x`, jumps to `body` stored in code cell reference, otherwise does nothing.

tvm_instructions.name: DICTPUSHCONST
tvm_instructions.short: Pushes a non-empty constant dictionary `d` (as a `Cell^?`) along with its `key_len`, stored as a part of the instruction. An empty dictionary can be pushed by a `PUSHNULL` instruction instead.

tvm_instructions.name: PFXDICTSWITCH
tvm_instructions.short: Performs prefix dictionary lookup and control transfer.

tvm_instructions.name: THROWANYIF
tvm_instructions.short: Throws an exception with error code `num` and parameter set to zero only if `cond` is NOT EQUAL to 0. Parameter represents the additional information passed to the exception handler.

tvm_instructions.name: THROWARGANYIF
tvm_instructions.short: Throws an exception with error code `num` and parameter set to `x` taken from the stack only if `cond` is NOT EQUAL to 0. Parameter represents the additional information passed to the exception handler.

tvm_instructions.name: EXTCALL
tvm_instructions.short: Special instruction for FFI (not released yet)

tvm_instructions.name: RUNVM
tvm_instructions.short: Runs child VM with `code` and stack `x_1...x_n`. Returns the resulting stack `x'_1...x'_m` and exitcode. Other arguments and return values are enabled by flags.

tvm_instructions.name: 2SWAP

tvm_instructions.name: 2DUP
tvm_instructions.signature_stack_string: y:Any x:Any -> y:Any x:Any y:Any x:Any

tvm_instructions.name: 2OVER
tvm_instructions.signature_stack_string: z:Any y:Any x:Any k:Any -> z:Any y:Any x:Any k:Any z:Any y:Any

tvm_instructions.name: STI
tvm_instructions.short: Stores a signed `width`-bit integer `x` into _Builder_ `b` and returns the resulting _Builder_ `b'`.

tvm_instructions.name: STI_ALT
tvm_instructions.short: Stores a signed `width`-bit integer `x` into _Builder_ `b` and returns the resulting _Builder_ `b'`. A longer version of `[width] STI`.

tvm_instructions.name: STU
tvm_instructions.short: Stores an unsigned `width`-bit integer `x` into _Builder_ `b` and returns the resulting _Builder_ `b'`.

tvm_instructions.name: STU_ALT
tvm_instructions.short: Stores an unsigned `width`-bit integer `x` into _Builder_ `b` and returns the resulting _Builder_ `b'`. A longer version of `[width] STU`.

tvm_instructions.name: LDI
tvm_instructions.short: Loads a signed `width`-bit integer `x` from _Slice_ `s` and pushes loaded value on stack along with _Slice_ with remainder data.

tvm_instructions.name: LDU
tvm_instructions.short: Loads an unsigned `width`-bit integer `x` from _Slice_ `s` and pushes loaded value on stack along with _Slice_ with remainder data.

tvm_instructions.name: QLSHIFT_VAR
tvm_instructions.short: Shift the top element of the stack left by a number of bits equal to the second element of the stack. Returns `NaN` if any operand is `NaN`.

tvm_instructions.name: QLSHIFT
tvm_instructions.short: Shift the top element of the stack left by `c` bits. Returns `NaN` if operand is `NaN`.

tvm_instructions.name: QRSHIFT_VAR
tvm_instructions.short: Shift the top element of the stack right by a number of bits equal to the second element of the stack. Returns `NaN` if any operand is `NaN`.

tvm_instructions.name: QRSHIFT
tvm_instructions.short: Shift the top element of the stack right by `c` bits. Returns `NaN` if operand is `NaN`.

tvm_instructions.name: THROW_SHORT
tvm_instructions.short: Throws an exception with error code `num`.

tvm_instructions.name: THROW
tvm_instructions.short: Throws an exception with error code `num`.

tvm_instructions.name: THROWIF_SHORT
tvm_instructions.short: Conditionally throws an exception with error code `num` if `cond` is NOT EQUAL to 0.

tvm_instructions.name: THROWIF
tvm_instructions.short: Conditionally throws an exception with error code `num` if `cond` is NOT EQUAL to 0.

tvm_instructions.name: THROWIFNOT_SHORT
tvm_instructions.short: Conditionally throws an exception with error code `num` if `cond` is EQUAL to 0.

tvm_instructions.name: THROWIFNOT
tvm_instructions.short: Conditionally throws an exception with error code `num` if `cond` is EQUAL to 0.

tvm_instructions.name: PUSHINT_4
tvm_instructions.short: Pushes tiny signed integer `x` onto the stack. Note that the instruction does not have the usual 4-bit range for the argument, but `-5 <= x <= 10`!

tvm_instructions.name: PUSHINT_8
tvm_instructions.short: Pushes small 8-bit signed integer `x` onto the stack.

tvm_instructions.name: PUSHINT_16
tvm_instructions.short: Pushes 16-bit signed integer `x` onto the stack.

tvm_instructions.name: PUSHINT_LONG
tvm_instructions.short: Pushes big signed integer `x`.

tvm_instructions.name: XCHG_0I_LONG
tvm_instructions.short: Interchanges top element with element at index `i`.

tvm_instructions.name: XCHG_0I
tvm_instructions.short: Interchanges top element with element at index `i`.

tvm_instructions.name: XCHG_IJ
tvm_instructions.short: Interchanges elements at indices `i` and `j`.

tvm_instructions.name: XCHG_1I
tvm_instructions.short: Interchanges second element with element at index `i`.

tvm_instructions.name: DUMPSTK
tvm_instructions.short: Dumps the entire contents of the stack to debug logs.

tvm_instructions.name: DEBUG
tvm_instructions.short: Base instruction for debugging purposes.

tvm_instructions.name: STRDUMP
tvm_instructions.short: Dumps slice value as a UTF-8 encoded string to debug logs.

tvm_instructions.name: DUMP
tvm_instructions.short: Dumps a `i`-th value from stack to debug logs.

tvm_instructions.name: PUSH
tvm_instructions.short: Copy value of `s(i)` and pushes it onto the stack.

tvm_instructions.name: PUSH_LONG
tvm_instructions.short: Copy value of `s(i)` and pushes it onto the stack.

tvm_instructions.name: POP
tvm_instructions.short: Removes the top element from the stack and stores it in `s(i)`. If `i` equal to 0, POP is effectively a `DROP`, i.e. the top element is removed from the stack.

tvm_instructions.name: POP_LONG
tvm_instructions.short: Removes the top element from the stack and stores it in `s(i).`

tvm_instructions.name: PUSHSLICE
tvm_instructions.short: Pushes the `slice` onto the stack.

layout.tlb: #8c r: (## 2) bits: (## 5) refs: ((r + 1) * ^Cell) data: ((8 * bits + 1) * Bit)

tvm_instructions.name: PUSHSLICE_LONG
tvm_instructions.short: Pushes the `slice` onto the stack.

tvm_instructions.name: PUSHCONT
tvm_instructions.short: Pushes a continuation onto the stack.

tvm_instructions.name: PUSHCONT_SHORT
tvm_instructions.short: Pushes a short continuation onto the stack.
